.TH KEEP 1 "@DATE@" "keep @VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
keep \- self-custodial key manager for Nostr and Bitcoin
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B keep
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.I COMMAND
[\fIARGS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B keep
stores Nostr and Bitcoin keys in an encrypted vault and signs with them
without exposing the key material to the requesting application. Keys may be
split across several devices using FROST threshold signatures, so that no
single device holds the whole secret.
.PP
The vault defaults to
.IR ~/.keep .
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-path " " \fIPATH\fR
Use the vault at \fIPATH\fR instead of the default.
.TP
.B \-\-hidden
Operate on the hidden vault.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-mlock
Do not lock secrets into memory. Accepts degraded security in exchange for
running where mlock is unavailable.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print help.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Print version.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B init
Create a new encrypted vault.
.TP
.B generate ", " import ", " list ", " export ", " delete
Manage Nostr keys in the vault.
.TP
.B secret
Store, reveal, list, and remove arbitrary secrets.
.TP
.B serve
Start the NIP-46 bunker and optional FROST network co-signer.
.TP
.B frost
FROST threshold-signature operations: key generation, signing, and network
coordination.
.TP
.B bitcoin ", " wallet
Bitcoin address derivation, descriptor management, PSBT signing, and spend
coordination.
.TP
.B backup ", " restore
Write and restore passphrase-encrypted vault backups.
.TP
.B rotate\-password ", " rotate\-data\-key
Change the unlock password, or re-encrypt every secret under a new data key.
.TP
.B audit
Inspect, verify, export, or prune the audit log.
.PP
Run
.B keep help
.I COMMAND
for the full option list of any subcommand.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B KEEP_PASSWORD
Vault password, for non-interactive use. Prefer
.B KEEP_PASSWORD_FILE
so the secret stays off the process environment.
.TP
.B KEEP_YES
Assume yes for confirmation prompts.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.keep
Default vault directory.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR keep-web (8)
.PP
Full documentation at
.UR https://github.com/privkeyio/keep
.UE
.SH SECURITY
Report vulnerabilities to security@privkey.io.
